<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idee61183f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s938"><num value="938">§ 938.</num><heading> Full faith and credit of the United States</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any contract of insurance or guarantee executed by the Secretary under this subchapter shall be an obligation supported by the full faith and credit of the United States and incontestable except for fraud or misrepresentation of which the holder had actual knowledge at the time it became a holder.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idee611840-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1936-05-20/ch432">May 20, 1936, ch. 432</ref>, title III, § 308, as added <ref href="/us/pl/93/32/s2">Pub. L. 93–32, § 2</ref>, <date date="1973-05-11">May 11, 1973</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/87/70">87 Stat. 70</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/94/124/s2">Pub. L. 94–124, § 2</ref>, <date date="1975-11-04">Nov. 4, 1975</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/89/677">89 Stat. 677</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/354/tII/s235/a/13">Pub. L. 103–354, title II, § 235(a)(13)</ref>, <date date="1994-10-13">Oct. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/3221">108 Stat. 3221</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idee611841-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idee611842-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idee611843-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1994—<ref href="/us/pl/103/354">Pub. L. 103–354</ref> substituted “Secretary” for “Administrator”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1975—<ref href="/us/pl/94/124">Pub. L. 94–124</ref> substituted “of which the holder had actual knowledge at the time it became a holder” for “of which the holder has actual knowledge”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idee611844-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idee611845-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1973-05-11">May 11, 1973</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/93/32/s12">section 12 of Pub. L. 93–32</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s930">section 930 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
